&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Since our founding in 1996, we have been at the vanguard of financial technology, providing groundbreaking expertise, quantitative analytics and software that redefine pricing and risk management in the financial markets. With the strategic acquisitions of FINCAD, PolyPaths and Kynex, Numerix has further strengthened its leadership position empowering financial institutions worldwide, to transform risk into opportunities with confidence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;We’re hiring a &lt;strong&gt;Market Data Product Specialist&lt;/strong&gt; in India (remote role) to help shape how Numerix sources, manages, and delivers the market data that powers pricing, analytics, and risk workflows for our clients. The ideal candidate possesses a solid understanding of market data and reference data, Python proficiency, quantitative analysis skills, and practical familiarity with using AI-enabled tools to improve productivity, accelerate analysis, and support data quality workflows, along with hands-on experience at a market data vendor or within a financial institution. This role is instrumental in ensuring data quality and integration, thereby elevating the value we deliver to clients. We’re looking for a highly analytical, communicative individual capable of handling market data complexities, driving data quality improvements within Numerix products, and supporting client deliverables. The Market Data Product Specialist will play a key role in expanding our market data products and delivering customer value in a forward-thinking, technology-driven environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
